==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peddlery
<hw>Ped"dler*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>pedlary</ets> and <ets>pedlery</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
trade, or the goods, of a peddler; hawking; small retail business, like
that of a peddler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Trifling; trickery.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Look . . . into these their deceitful
<xex>peddleries</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peddling</ent>⟦br⟧
